 :tx/rationale "Create task: C9-CONCEPT-SPLIT-v2: Strategy 4 — TF-IDF partition + dual trigger + learned thresholds. TWO INDEPENDENT FAILURES in current splitting: (1) Trigger failure — variance doesn't capture 'too many topics'. (2) Partition failure — embedding cosine doesn't distinguish topics within a domain. APPROACH: (A) Dual trigger: should_split returns true when variance > split_threshold OR member_count > max_concept_size. (B) TF-IDF similarity matrix replaces embedding cosine for Fiedler partition — same discriminative signal used by generate_concept_name (INV-REFLEXIVE-007 consistency). (C) All thresholds C9-compliant: split_threshold default 0.5 from config, max_concept_size default 50 from Piaget formal operational (STEERING_MANIFOLD §3), min_split_size default 3 from MIN_CLUSTER_SIZE. (D) Calibration path: at harvest, record (threshold_used, pre_split_variance, post_split_mean_variance, num_sub_concepts). After 5+ events, Otsu's method calibrates optimal thresholds (same pattern as calibrate_join_threshold). IMPLEMENTATION: (1) Add MAX_CONCEPT_SIZE=50 constant to concept.rs. (2) Change should_split signature to accept both thresholds. (3) In split_concept: replace embedding cosine matrix with TF-IDF cosine matrix (~15 lines). Extract TF-IDF vector builder from generate_concept_name into shared helper. (4) Update split_concepts binary to read concept.max-size from config. (5) Wire into observe lifecycle: after crystallization, check should_split with dual trigger. ACCEPTANCE: (A) 587-member cluster splits into topic-coherent sub-concepts. (B) Sub-concept names describe distinguishing terms (TF-IDF). (C) No concept exceeds 50 members after splitting. (D) All thresholds from config with fallback. (E) Fiedler bisect operates on TF-IDF matrix not embedding matrix. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs, crates/braid/src/bin/split_concepts.rs, crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs"
